(26959, 3654, 'mission', 'Anticipate and respond effectively to technological changes with agile, innovative, robust, secure services and applications to enhance research, inspire the next generation of researchers and advance operational and administrative activities at Malawi Liverpool Wellcome Trust.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(26960, 3654, '_mission', 'field_5e27f960986d9'),
(26961, 3654, 'vision', 'To be recognized with operational excellence in providing secure and reliable IT services as an enabler for excellent research that benefit researchers, and the next generation researchers.'),
(26962, 3654, '_vision', 'field_5e27f971986da'),
(26963, 3654, 'core', '<h2></h2>\r\n<strong>Create a secure computing environment</strong>\r\n\r\nProvide a secure computing environment to ensure staff feel safer and work more efficiently without fear of external threats and are at great liberty to foster new, innovative ideas, with the knowledge that their work is secure.\r\n\r\n<strong>Foster data-driven decision making</strong>\r\n\r\nData-driven decision making ensures unbiased accuracy, encourages information to be continually added and updated, and leads to long-term results, allow staff to be increasingly competitive with peer institutions within and acros\r\n\r\n<strong>Establish shared ICT Governance</strong>\r\n\r\nShared governance builds trust, confidence, and accountability to strengthen the organization through diversity of thought and collaboration. Shared governance will particularly focus on (1) needed and desired investments in ICT (2) IT Security, Business continuity and Compliance requirements that needs to be enforceable (3) Training and Awareness programs (4) Participation of every member in the success of IT enterprise.\r\n\r\n<strong>Continuous Improvement and Investment</strong>\r\n\r\ncontinuously make improvements and investments to generate business value through reduced costs, process innovations and, access and availability to Information technology resources.\r\n\r\n<strong>Develop a competitive IT Team</strong>\r\n\r\nMLW mission is “to conduct internationally excellent research to benefit health” and to accomplish this, we must strive for excellence in all areas. We will provide excellent IT Services by ensuring we have competent IT Staff who are ready to respond to emerging technological demands.\r\n\r\n<strong>Operations, Academic and Research partnerships</strong>\r\n\r\nTo ensure opportunities for research and operational activities conducted at MLW are realized.'),
