(27874, 3717, 'achievements_10_title', 'Lung Health'),
(27875, 3717, '_achievements_10_title', 'field_5e255c394e9bf'),
(27876, 3717, 'achievements_10_text', '<p class=\"p1\">MLW has  published the largest study of chronic lung disease in Africa and made the novel observation that 38% of Malawians have abnormal spirometry, mainly restrictive (small) lungs. Small lungs are associated with chronic lung disease and acute pneumonia (Jary - Thorax in press) and the high observed prevalence indicates that as the population ages, a large burden of pneumonia driven by underlying lung disease will present. The largest intervention study ever to reduce household air pollution has been published; use of an improved cook stove had no effect in reducing childhood pneumonia.</p>\r\n(PIs: Gordon S, Rylance)'),
(27877, 3717, '_achievements_10_text', 'field_5e255c414e9c0'),
(27878, 3717, 'achievements_11_title', 'Chronic HIV and stroke '),
(27879, 3717, '_achievements_11_title', 'field_5e255c394e9bf'),
(27880, 3717, 'achievements_11_text', '<p class=\"p1\">Stroke is common, severe and particularly disabling for Malawians given the lack of rehabilitation specialty care. The association of stroke with a high prevalence of hypertension in the elderly is expected, but novel recent MLW studies have identified HIV as the leading correlate of hospitalised stroke in younger adults. Current work continues to explore the association between inflammation and stroke in this population.</p>\r\n(PIs: Mwandumba, Benjamin)'),
