(314, 1, '2020-01-27 08:57:48', '2020-01-27 08:57:48', 'Martha Khombe Moyo is a research nurse who has been in research field since 2012.Martha has been working mostly in paediatric based studies. She was involved in a study which was looking at the Developmental effects of children whose mothers were on ART and were being breast fed against those whose mothers were HIV negative and were also being breast fed.(PIE-AB study),Limbe Health Centre, Blantyre, from 2014 to 2016. She then joined the Virology Research Group in 2017 under Rotamune study which is also a paediatric based study. With the experience of working in paediatric studies, Martha has developed an interest to further her career in children care, currently studying for Bachelor’s Degree in Early Childhood Development at Malawi Assemblies of God University; this will widen her knowledge in paediatric based studies which are underway at MLW.\r\n\r\nMartha has a certificate in Nursing and Midwifery and a Diploma in Leadership Management. She is a registered member with the Nurses and Midwives Council of Malawi.\r\nHer long term goal is to further her career in paediatric management.', 'Martha Khombe Moyo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'martha-khombe-moyo', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:00:06', '2020-03-11 11:00:06', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=314', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(315, 1, '2020-01-27 09:00:42', '2020-01-27 09:00:42', 'Chimwemwe Mhango is Masters student under the Virology Research Group at MLW. He is currently enrolled at the University of Malawi, College of Medicine where he is studying Bioinformatics. His interests lie in Molecular Biology where he has been characterizing rotavirus strains circulating in Malawi. His current work is on evolutionary mechanisms that led to the reemergence of new rotavirus strains and how these strains are related to similar strains emerging in other African countries.\r\n\r\nChimwemwe obtained his Bachelor of Medical Laboratory Sciences in 2017 from the University of Malawi, College of medicine. He was one of the recipients of the MLW/COM undergraduate research grants in 2017.\r\n\r\nChimwemwe’s long term goal is to become an expert in viral evolution and viral pathology. He wants to understand the impact of viral evolution on the pathology of viruses.', 'Chimwemwe Mhango', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'chimwemwe-mhango', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:02:13', '2020-03-11 11:02:13', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=315', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(316, 1, '2020-01-27 09:01:13', '2020-01-27 09:01:13', 'End Chinyama is a Laboratory Technician at MLW under Virology Research group. End has worked in a number of projects at MLW which include VacSurv, PCVPA, ROVI and RV3.\r\nEnd has a Diploma in Biomedical Sciences from the Malawi Adventist University (Malamulo College of Health Sciences) and he has just completed a BSc in Public health from Share World Open University.\r\n\r\nHis long-term goal is to become a vibrant researcher in Molecular Biology and contribute a lot in the area of disease prevention at national and international level.', 'End Chinyama', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'end-chinyama', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:02:41', '2020-03-11 11:02:41', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=316', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(317, 1, '2020-01-27 09:02:46', '2020-01-27 09:02:46', 'Esther Thaulo is a pre-MSc intern within the Virology Research Group at Malawi-Liverpool-Wellcome Trust Clinical Research Programme. Her research is linked to the ROTAMUNE study which is investigating host immune responses to rotavirus vaccination and rotavirus natural infections.\r\n\r\nEsther has a Bachelor’s degree in Medical Laboratory Sciences from the University of Malawi, College of Medicine.\r\n\r\nHer long-term goal is to pursue a PhD in immunology and become an established researcher.', 'Esther Thaulo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'esther-thaulo', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:03:11', '2020-03-11 11:03:11', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=317', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
