(319, 1, '2020-01-27 09:04:29', '2020-01-27 09:04:29', 'He is working under CRYPTORESP study, a longitudinal trial to evaluate Pulmonary and intestinal cryptosporidium infections concurrently. He holds a BSc in Biomedical Sciences obtained at Mzuzu university,2014. He is currently pursuing a MSc in Antimicrobial stewardship at College of Medicine, University of Malawi. He plans to apply for a PhD in 2022. His interested in infectious diseases.', 'James Tchado Nyirenda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'james-tchado-nyirenda', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:03:45', '2020-03-11 11:03:45', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=319', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(320, 1, '2020-01-27 09:04:48', '2020-01-27 09:04:48', 'Jonathan Mandolo is a research scientist under virology group at Malawi Liverpool welcome trust. He is interested in virology. He would like to use his molecular and immunological techniques trying to understand why vaccines like rotavirus vaccine efficacy is low in developing countries like Malawi. Particularly, he is interested to understand how maternal microbiome affects vaccine efficacy by looking at relationship between maternal breast milk microbiota and infant gut microbiota and see how that affect rotavirus vaccine response.\r\nJonathan Mandolo hold Bachelor of Science in medical laboratory sciences (honours) obtained at the university of Malawi-College of medicine obtained in 2014. He is now doing Master of Science in Bioinformatics at the University of Malawi-College of medicine, which he is expecting to complete in 2020. From then, he would like to apply for PhD and specialize in Molecular biology. Long-term plan is to become an independent researcher in Molecular biology field and later become a Leader in the field.', 'Jonathan Mandolo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jonathan-mandolo', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:04:18', '2020-03-11 11:04:18', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=320', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(322, 1, '2020-01-27 09:08:56', '2020-01-27 09:08:56', 'Leah is the Research Nurse within the Viral Immunology Group. She obtained a diploma in Registered Nursing and Midwifery from the Malawi College of Health Sciences in 2016. She is in the penultimate year of a Bachelor of Science Degree in Social Sciences-Development Studies at Catholic University of Malawi. Leah is registered with Malawi Nurses and Midwifery Council of Malawi and has clinical trial experience.\r\n\r\nCurrently, she is part of a study investigating the role of developmentally regulated microRNAs in neonatal immunity. Her major interest is in relating the community perceptions, values and beliefs to research. Leah’s long-term goal is to pursue a Master’s degree in Medical Anthropology or Global Health.', 'Leah Mulira', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leah-mulira', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:44:01', '2020-03-11 11:44:01', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=322', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(323, 1, '2020-01-27 09:10:02', '2020-01-27 09:10:02', 'Lusako is a Research Assistant within the Viral Immunology group. He obtained a Bachelor of Science Degree in Medical Laboratory Science from the University of Eastern Africa (Kenya) in 2016.\r\n\r\nLusako is part of a study investigating factors that explain ongoing high prevalence of pneumococcal colonisation in HIV-infected adults on antiretroviral therapy. He is also involved in a study investigating the impact of HIV on alveolar phagocyte responses against Streptococcus pneumoniae. His main research interest is host-pathogen interactions, and is currently working on building his microbiology and immunology skills.\r\n\r\nHis immediate goal is to pursue a Master of Science degree in Immunology and subsequently a PhD. His long-term goal is to become a research leader working on bacterial infections using microbiology and immunology tools.', 'Lusako Lucky Sibale', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lusako-lucky-sibale', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:44:45', '2020-03-11 11:44:45', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=323', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
