(327, 1, '2020-01-27 09:15:17', '2020-01-27 09:15:17', 'Has worked under CRYPTOFAZ study which was focusing on the effectiveness of Clofazimine in diarrheic individuals caused by cryptosporidium and currently he is working under CRYPTORESP study which is evaluating respiratory cryptosporidiosis in pediatric diarrheal disease. He holds a Diploma in Biomedical Sciences obtained at Malawi College of Health Sciences, 2013 and is currently pursuing a BSc in Environmental Science. His long term goal is to pursue a MSc and then a PhD, and major in Microbiology.', 'Mike Msakwiza', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mike-msakwiza', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:04:44', '2020-03-11 11:04:44', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=327', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(329, 1, '2020-01-27 09:17:33', '2020-01-27 09:17:33', 'Percy is a Research Assistant within the Viral Immunology group. He obtained a Diploma in Biomedical Sciences from Malawi College of Health Sciences in 2014. He has vast laboratory experience having worked with different projects within the MLW programme since 2014.\r\n\r\nPercy is part of team establishing the first Experimental Human Pneumococcal Model in Africa. His long-term goal is to pursue a career in Public health with focus in infectious diseases.', 'Percy Benard Mwenechanya', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'percy-benard-mwenechanya', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:45:47', '2020-03-11 11:45:47', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=329', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
