(343, 1, '2020-01-27 10:18:30', '2020-01-27 10:18:30', 'Has worked under CRYPTOFAZ study which was focusing on the effectiveness of Clofazimine in diarrheic individuals caused by cryptosporidium and currently he is working under BAMBI study which is looking at Maternal Risk Factors and Biomarkers for Prediction of Early Onset Neonatal Infection. He holds a BSc in Biomedical Sciences obtained at Mzuzu university,2014. His long term goal is to pursue a MSc and then a PhD, and major on emerging and re-emerging infectious diseases as a research focus.', 'Vita Nyasulu', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'vita-nyasulu', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:06:11', '2020-03-11 11:06:11', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=343', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(344, 1, '2020-01-27 10:18:54', '2020-01-27 10:18:54', 'Mary Matemba sarted her Nursing career with Phalombe Nursing school, she worked with CHARM hospital and the she joined Malawi Liverpool Welcome Trust, and has worked in different studies e.g Vacsurv, Rotarite combined study, ABCD and curernly in Diarsurv and Rotagene in all these studies we were identifying and recruiting eligible partcicipants as per the protocol. In Rotarite she was doing Rapid test.\r\n\r\nShe is a Nurse Midwifery and a Family planning provider', 'Mary Matemba', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mary-matemba', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:07:45', '2020-03-11 11:07:45', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=344', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(345, 1, '2020-01-27 10:19:34', '2020-01-27 10:19:34', 'Orpha Kumwenda started her Nursing career with St Johns Nursing School, she a holder of Nursing &amp; Midwifery certificates, worked with Ministry of Health at Nkhotakota hospital for 1 year. Then she joined Amar cooperation as Nurse Midwife. Then she joined Research programs in 2007 with College of Medicine in study of Bacterial Meningitis then she jpoined Malaria Alert where she was sent to Liwonde to do a drug efficacy in pregnant women. Now with Malawi Liverpool welcome Trust working with Rota rite combined study – identifying and recruiting eligible participants also doing Rapid testing, and also ABCD trial study.\r\n\r\nShe is a provider of ART and Family planning door to door.\r\n\r\nNow in Diarsurv and Rotagene studies.', 'Orpha Kumwenda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'orpha-kumwenda', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:08:29', '2020-03-11 11:08:29', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=345', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(346, 1, '2020-01-27 10:21:03', '2020-01-27 10:21:03', 'Chikondi is a PhD student jointly registered with University of Liverpool, UK and the College of Medicine (COM), University of Malawi and she is based at the Malawi-Liverpool-Wellcome Trust Clinical Research Programme (MLW). She holds a BSc. in Medical Laboratory Technology obtained in 2012 with credit. She then worked as a laboratory technologist and research intern with research projects at COM and MLW, respectively. During that time, she was awarded a scholarship to do Master of Philosophy (MPhil) in Public Health which she graduated in 2018. Her MPhil research work was on assessing the challenges in implementation of early infant HIV diagnosis in HIV-exposed infants in rural Malawi.\r\n\r\nHer current research interest, which transformed into her PhD research work, is to understand the immunological factors that could explain why rotavirus vaccine underperforms in low-income countries. She believes that better knowledge of the rotavirus vaccine-induced immunity would inform the design of more effective next generation rotavirus vaccine candidates. She aims to become one of the few female independent African Biomedical Research Scientist.', 'Chikondi Malamba-Matumika Banda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'chikondi-malamba-matumika-banda', '', '', '2020-03-11 11:09:07', '2020-03-11 11:09:07', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=346', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
