(443, 1, '2020-03-09 09:24:56', '2020-03-09 09:24:56', 'Funding from:\r\n\r\n1. Background – Education, supervision (if any), main interests in research.\r\nClinical trials/ Research project management. Previously have been involved in clinical trials monitoring for many and various clinical trials in various therapeutic areas. Have been also involved in research staff training in ICH-GCP/HSP, SOPs and applicable protocols.\r\n\r\n2. Education background – Current level of education, education obtained in the past from Bachelors level.\r\nMaster of Public Health with bias in Epidemiology &amp; Statistics and BSc. Health Science Education/Clinical Medicine\r\n\r\n3. Long term goals - e.g. project to pursue, attaining further education.\r\nContinue project management and attaining new skills and achievements in Clinical Research Project Management/Public Health.', 'Theressa Misiri', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'theressa-misiri', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:03:47', '2020-03-11 12:03:47', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=443', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(444, 1, '2020-03-09 09:25:10', '2020-03-09 09:25:10', 'Felistas Kumwenda Mwakiseghile works as a Trial coordinator in the TyVAC vaccine Trial and the Typhoid surveillance (STRATAA) study at MLW. She also helps coordinate other studies like TyCOI. She has Co-authored in different papers at MLW.\r\n\r\nShe has seven years trail coordination work experience and has high expertise in managing two big clinical Trials (TRACT and TyVAC). Her main roles have been recruiting and coordinating research subjects and serving as a principle administrative liaison for the project. She has also been overseeing and coordinating the provision of administrative and staff services to principle investigators; coordinating ethical submissions and developing and maintaining recordkeeping systems and procedures\r\n\r\nFelistas has a Bachelor of Science in Nursing from the University of Malawi, Kamuzu College of Nursing and a Master of Science in Nursing and International Health from University of Aberdeen UK\r\n\r\nHer long term goal is to develop herself in the area of project management and also undertake work in complex projects.', 'Felistas Kumwenda Mwakiseghile', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'felistas-kumwenda-mwakiseghile', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:04:23', '2020-03-11 12:04:23', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=444', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(445, 1, '2020-03-09 09:25:23', '2020-03-09 09:25:23', 'Funding from TyVAC\r\n\r\nAdvance Diploma in Human Resource Management with Association of Business Executives (ABE)\r\n\r\nLong Term Goals: To attain a Bachelors in Business Administration and masters in Management (Operations and Project Management).', 'Eunice Kadzakumanja', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'eunice-kadzakumanja', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:12:32', '2020-03-11 12:12:32', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=445', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(446, 1, '2020-03-09 09:25:42', '2020-03-09 09:25:42', 'David Banda is a motivated and results driven information systems specialist with a proven track record in data management and data analytics. He is currently working as Data Manager at MLW and is mainly responsible for managing data for STRATAA, TyVAC and RHICCA projects.\r\n\r\nHe has a Bachelor of Science Degree in Management Information Systems from the University of Malawi, The Polytechnic. He is also a Certified Information Systems Auditor.\r\n\r\nDavid is interested in developing valuable solutions to drive accuracy and efficiency of the research process. He also wants to pursue a Masters in Management Information Systems in the near future.', 'David Simon Banda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'david-simon-banda', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:12:57', '2020-03-11 12:12:57', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=446', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(447, 1, '2020-03-09 09:25:55', '2020-03-09 09:25:55', 'Funding from: TyVAC\r\n\r\nBackground: I hold Bachelors of Science in Medical Laboratory Science from University of Malawi, College of Medicine which was obtained in 2018.As part of my undergraduate studies I did a research study on the prevalence of antimicrobial resistant bacteria in Mudi river and my supervisor was Daniel Banda.\r\n\r\nCurrently I intend to do a masters degree in Molecular Biology. With the burden of infectious diseases in Sub-Sahara Africa I would like to do a PhD in molecular immunology focusing on the mechanisms of host-pathogen molecular interactions.', 'Belson Malcolm Kutambe', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'belson-malcolm-kutambe', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:13:25', '2020-03-11 12:13:25', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=447', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(448, 1, '2020-03-09 09:26:07', '2020-03-09 09:26:07', 'Funding from : STRATSUP\r\nI hold a bachelor of science degree in Medical Laboratory Sciences (Honours) obtained from the University of Malawi, College of Medicine in 2018. During my undergraduate studies, I carried out a research project entitled “Prevalence of Hepatitis C among diabetic patients at Queen Elizabeth Central Hospital (QECH)” supervised by Dr. Tonney Nyirenda. As part of my carrier and personal development plan, I would like to apply for a Master’s program in molecular biology. I plan to conduct a master’s research project that will benefit the Salmonella and Enteric Disease project Group and the general public.\r\n\r\nLong term goal(s):\r\nParticipate in research studies, gain more knowledge and apply for a PhD program to become a researcher.', 'Niza Mark Silungwe', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'niza-mark-silungwe', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:13:59', '2020-03-11 12:13:59', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=448', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(449, 1, '2020-03-09 09:26:22', '2020-03-09 09:26:22', 'Work Email: njambo@mlw.mw\r\n\r\nNdaru Jambo is a PhD student on the College of Medicine/University of Liverpool joint scheme under the supervision of Professor Melita Gordon and Dr Tonney Nyirenda. Her PhD is focused on characterising cellular and humoral immune responses against Salmonella infection.\r\nNdaru has a Master’s degree in Infection, Immunity and Human Disease from the University of Leeds. She also has a Bachelor of Science degree from the Chancellor college, University of Malawi.\r\n\r\nHer long-term goal is to develop into an independent researcher with a focus in host-pathogen interactions.', 'Ndaru Jambo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ndaru-jambo', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:14:23', '2020-03-11 12:14:23', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=449', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(450, 1, '2020-03-09 09:26:37', '2020-03-09 09:26:37', 'Angeziwa is funded by the MLW core training grant and Commonwealth Scholarship Commission.\r\n\r\nAngeziwa is a joint PhD student registered with the University of Malawi and University of Liverpool. Her research project “The role of Gastrointestinal tract microbiota in colonization resistance against enteric bacterial pathogens” is supervised by Prof Melita Gordon who heads the Salmonella and Enteric Pathogens group at MLW. She works in collaboration with researchers from COM, UoL, Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute, and the Quadram Institute Biosciences.\r\n\r\nShe holds a Masters in Infectious Diseases from London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine, (funded by CSC) and a Bachelor of Science Degree in Environmental Science and Technology from University of Malawi, The Polytechnic (funded by the Malawi government).\r\nAngeziwa’s research area of interest is in how the gut microbiota controls infections. She would specifically like to study the gut microbiota and its associated immune responses to natural or vaccine-induced Salmonella challenge. Her long term goals are to conduct cutting edge research, be one of the first female Malawian biomedical research leaders, and to train the next generation of scientists that can compete on an international level.', 'Angeziwa Chunga Chirambo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'angeziwa-chunga-chirambo', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:14:47', '2020-03-11 12:14:47', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=450', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(451, 1, '2020-03-09 09:26:57', '2020-03-09 09:26:57', 'Dalitso Longwe is a field worker at MLW under the supervision of DR Tonney Nyirenda under PATCH-M study which looks at Salmonella (Typhi and non Typhoidal)\r\n\r\nDalitso has an advanced Diploma in Public Health obtained at Skyway University,and she also has a certificate in HIV Testing Services which was obtained under MACRO, this also is helping her when recruiting clients as those who are eligible are recruited, the criteria looks at those who are ART naive, Experienced as well as Negative.\r\n\r\nHer long term goal is pursue a Degree in Public health as well as Masters in public health, which will help to implement the right knowledge and also to bring awareness about the importance of public health to a wider range of audience in developing as well as developed countries in a research set up.', 'Dalitso Longwe', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dalitso-longwe', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:15:12', '2020-03-11 12:15:12', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=451', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(452, 1, '2020-03-09 09:27:08', '2020-03-09 09:27:08', 'Joyce is a research nurse at MLW under supervision of Dr Tonney Nyirenda who is the Principle Investigator in Malawi and Professor Melita Gordon as Overall Chief Investigator who looks into Salmonera. I have gone a very long way during my career training from Certificate in general nursing and midwifery obtained in the year between 1988 to 1991 at Zomba School of Nursing, to University Diploma in Nursing Sciences, at the Malawi College of Health Sciences obtained in year between 2010-2013, then Bachelors’ Degree in Public Health, at ShareWorld Open University obtained in year between 2014-2016.\r\n\r\nMy profession path started in October 1992 to February 2002 working as an Enrolled Nurse / Midwife with the Ministry of Health (MOH), worked at Zomba Central Hospital, Thyolo District Hospital and Limbe Health Centre. I joined the Malawi Liverpool Wellcome Trust on 1st February 2002 as a research nurse. In January 2015 to October 2017 worked as Line Manager at Paediatric Research Ward (PRW) at Queen Elizabeth Central Hospital (QECH) Blantyre, managing critically ill children both for research as well as clinical care. In November 2017 to February 2018 acted as Assistance Clinical Manager. (MLW) i also obtained skills in Computer literate; hearing test and done short courses such as Good Clinical Practises (GCP) and managerial skills, just to mention a few.\r\n\r\nMy aspiration is to go through a ladder to Master in Public Health. Professionally I am a hardworking nurse with vast experience as a nurse in clinical area as well as in research. I am highly motivated and professional work within the Professional Code of Conduct guidelines and policies.\r\n\r\nIn Public health research my main interest is to see the community being prevented in related problems apart from giving them nursing care when they fall sick.', 'Joyce Mbumba Macheso', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'joyce-mbumba-macheso', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:15:42', '2020-03-11 12:15:42', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=452', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(453, 1, '2020-03-09 09:29:34', '2020-03-09 09:29:34', 'I am currently working at Strata/ Tyvac project under Melita Gordon as our Principal Investigator.\r\n\r\nI have an advanced diploma in business information technology obtained from national college of information technology, I am currently enrolled at the same institution for abachelors degree in computing. My long term goal is to obtain a masters degree in computer science.', 'Mtende Priscilla Mwandira', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mtende-priscilla-mwandira', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:16:16', '2020-03-11 12:16:16', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=453', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(454, 1, '2020-03-09 09:29:42', '2020-03-09 09:29:42', 'Working with Strataa /Tyvac study\r\n\r\nMelita Gordon is our Principal investigator\r\n\r\nAs a field worker my duty is to collect data, asking for consent from participants,following up clients who were recruited in the study.providing study information to clients\r\nBachelors degree in social work\r\n\r\nTo pursue my career and have masters in Special needs education', 'Elizabeth Mateyu', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'elizabeth-mateyu', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:16:41', '2020-03-11 12:16:41', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=454', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(455, 1, '2020-03-09 09:29:54', '2020-03-09 09:29:54', 'Chisomo Jassi is a research nurse under the supervision of Dr Fumbani Limani .\r\nHer research deals with estimating the economic burden of typhoid\r\nFever in urban Blantyre.\r\n\r\nShe has also worked with TyVAC study under the supervision of Felistas Kumwenda.\r\nThe study was a vaccine trail on Typhoid conjugate vaccine in children in urban Blantyre.\r\nShe has also worked with Malaria Alert Centre under ICEMR study in Liwonde Namanolo Health center, the study that was trying to understand why Malaria is still a burden in Malawi while there are lots of preventive ways to prevent and treat Malaria.\r\n\r\nChisomo Jassi has a diploma in Nursing and Midwifery Technician from Malamulo College of Health Sciences\r\n\r\nHer long term goals is to pursue a Degree in Public Health and then pursue a Masters Degree in Research Project Management and develop into a research leader and training the next generation of Health and scientist in Malawi and internationally.', 'Chisomo Coutinho Jassi', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'chisomo-coutinho-jassi', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:17:16', '2020-03-11 12:17:16', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=455', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(456, 1, '2020-03-09 09:30:03', '2020-03-09 09:30:03', 'Kelvin Winga is a field worker under the supervision of Dr Fumbani Limani .\r\nHer research deals with estimating the economic burden of typhoid\r\nFever in urban Blantyre.\r\nHe has also worked with TyVAC study under the supervision of Felistas Kumwenda.\r\nThe study was a vaccine trail on Typhoid conjugate vaccine in children in urban Blantyre.\r\nKelvin Winga has Advanced Diploma in Information Technology Soche Technical College 2016', 'Kelvin Mwanthowa Winga', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kelvin-mwanthowa-winga', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:17:41', '2020-03-11 12:17:41', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=456', 0, 'researchers', '', 0);
