(458, 1, '2020-03-09 09:31:24', '2020-03-09 09:31:24', 'STRATAA/TYVAC -MLW\r\nSTRATEGIC ALLIANCE TYPHOID AFRICA AND ASIA/TYPHOID VACCINE CONSORTIUM. The research is about fighting against Typhoid in Africa and Asia. The Project Investigator is Melita Gordon.\r\nEDUCATION\r\nAdvanced diploma in HIV and Management – 2009', 'Mphatso Kasenda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mphatso-kasenda', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:18:52', '2020-03-11 12:18:52', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=458', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(459, 1, '2020-03-09 09:31:45', '2020-03-09 09:31:45', 'STRATAA-TYVAC (wellcome Trust) 2016-2019\r\nBernald Dossie is a Fieldworker for STRATEGIC ALLIANCE TYPHOID AFRICA AND ASIA(STRATAA) &amp;TYPHOID VACCINE ACCELERATION CONSORTIUM (TYVAC) at MLW and the Principal Investigator is Melita Gordon. The study is about fighting against Typhoid in Africa and Asia.\r\n\r\nEDUCATION\r\nChartered institute of Logistics and Transport\r\nDiploma A&amp;B 2014 -2016.\r\nCertificate 2014.\r\n\r\nCAREER GOALS\r\nTo peruse my career and have more experience and skills in field working.', 'Bernald Dossie', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bernald-dossie', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:19:21', '2020-03-11 12:19:21', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=459', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(460, 1, '2020-03-09 09:57:11', '2020-03-09 09:57:11', 'Funding from : Center for Vaccine Development (VCD) University of Maryland School of Medical, Baltimore, MD, USA.\r\nNurse Midwife Technician, lead Nurse Strataa Tyvac Studies Ndirande Site. Under Dr Melita Gordon. Nurses Continuous Professional Development Coordinator. Contribute to the success of the organisation through supervising daily study activities, recruiting study participants, data collection and sample collection.\r\n\r\nI have also worked with Dr Wilson Mandala, Dr Laura Benjamin, Janet Storm and Chris Nixon.\r\n\r\nI have a bachelor\'s degree in Public health from Share world open university.\r\nMy long term plan is to pursue a Masters in Epidemiology.', 'Patricia Phula', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'patricia-phula', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:21:38', '2020-03-11 12:21:38', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=460', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(461, 1, '2020-03-09 09:57:20', '2020-03-09 09:57:20', 'I am a Research Nurse at MLW in TyVac study whose principal Investigator is Dr Melita Gordon. The study examines efficacy of Typhoid Vaccine.\r\n\r\nI have also worked in different clinical trials like, differentiating treatment failure from re_ infection of antimalarial drug LA, whose Principal investigator was Prof Don Mathanga. I worked in a clinical trial examining efficacy of two antimalarial drugs Chlopraguanil Dapson and Artesunate if can be combined in one pill. The Principal investigator was Dr Dan Wooton by then at MLW. I also worked with Prof Don Mathanga at Malaria Alert center in a clinical trial examing if Dehydroartemesin piperaquin can replace SP as a prophylaxis in antenatal mothers.\r\nI have Nursing and Midwifery certificate obtained at St Luke\'s and Mulanje colleges of nursing and midwifery.\r\n\r\nMy long term goals are to obtain Community Nursing diploma certificate and Bachelor\'s degree certificate in public health, these will help me in my interest in research which mostly I work with the community.', 'Georgina Makuta', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'georgina-makuta', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:22:06', '2020-03-11 12:22:06', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=461', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
(462, 1, '2020-03-09 09:57:49', '2020-03-09 09:57:49', 'QUALIFICATIONS\r\nMalawi School Certificate of Education\r\nHealth Surveillance Assistant Certificate\r\nHIV and Aids testing and counselling certificate\r\nART counselling certificate\r\nCURRENT ORGANIZATION ( mlw)\r\nFrom 2018 to date: TyVAC &amp; STRAATA study( field worker)\r\nFrom 2016 to 2018 (STRAATA)\r\n(Field worker)\r\n\r\nFrom 2013 to 2016 (Vacsurv study)\r\nField worker\r\nORGANIZATION: ( Malamulo HIV &amp;AIDS prevention &amp; family planning promotion funded by\r\n\r\nUSAID through PACT Malawi\r\n2007 to 2008: HIV &amp;AIDS testing and counselling officer\r\n2008 to 2011: Information Education &amp; Communication officer &amp; Youth officer.\r\n2011 to 2013: HIV &amp; AIDS prevention officer.\r\n\r\nORGANIZATION ( Conforzi plantations)\r\n2004 to 2007 ( HTC &amp; ART counsellor)\r\n2000 to 2003 ( Malaria project I-MAL study) community mobilization officer1997 to 2000( senior health surveillance assistant &amp; sefty &amp; health assistant)', 'Fraction Witness Kadzuwa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'fraction-witness-kadzuwa', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:22:32', '2020-03-11 12:22:32', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=462', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
