(503, 1, '2020-03-11 12:20:40', '2020-03-11 12:20:40', 'Funded by MLW (Wellcome Trust Uk)\r\n\r\nYamikani Mary Banda is a Field Worker with TyVac at Malawi Liverpool Wellcome Trust under the Coordination of Ms. Felistas Mwakasayire. The project deals with Salmonera virus which is normally found in water and unsafe salads. So far the project has injected 27,000 children in the areas of Ndirande, Zingwangwa, Naperi, Chitawira and Manase.\r\n\r\nYamikani has a Diploma in Community Development from Mzuzu Polytechnic, Malawi. And a certificate in HIV Counseling Service done in 2017 in Nsanje with funding from UNICEF.\r\nBefore joining Malawi Liverpool Wellcome Trust, Yamikani worked as a Field Officer with Goal Malawi and was based in Nsanje, she also worked with Rain Forest Alliance as Relief Social Development Officer and in 2012 she joined Save the Children as Relief and Distribution Monitor.\r\n\r\nHer long term goal is to pursue a Bachelor’s Degree in Community Development or Public Health.', 'Yamikani Mary Banda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'yamikani-mary-banda', '', '', '2020-03-11 12:20:40', '2020-03-11 12:20:40', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=researchers&#038;p=503', 0, 'researchers', '', 0),
