(522, 1, '2020-03-18 08:45:48', '2020-03-18 08:45:48', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MLW is an internationally prominent\nhealth research institution led by Malawian &amp; International Scientists,\npursuing scientific excellence and improving the health of people in\nsub-Saharan Africa.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MLW\nis built around excellent laboratories, strategically located in the largest\nhospital in Malawi, Queen Elizabeth Central Hospital. It is closely linked with\nthe community and is an integral part of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.medcol.mw/\">College of Medicine</a>. These relationships provide a unique opportunity replicated in few\ncentres in Africa to study major health issues spanning both community and\nhospital.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since\nits inception, MLW has maintained partnership with the Liverpool School of\nTropical Medicine, the University of Liverpool and the Wellcome Trust. MLW is\nbased in Blantyre with field research sites around urban Blantyre, Thyolo,\nChikhwawa, Zomba, Mangochi and Machinga.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Welcome', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '7-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-18 08:45:48', '2020-03-18 08:45:48', '', 7, 'http://127.0.0.1/7-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(523, 1, '2020-03-18 08:46:23', '2020-03-18 08:46:23', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MLW will Conduct research to benefit health and train the next generation of researchers. Over 20 years, research discoveries and policy changes leading to implementation of effective interventions have resulted in major impact against infectious disease not only in Malawi but across the world.<br>Particular successes have been reductions in malaria infection and death, reduction in rotavirus infection and diarrhoeal death and reduction in pneumonia and pneumococcal infection.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We have expanded over 20 years to now have 2 Programmes –&nbsp;<a href=\"http://127.0.0.1/about/\">prevention of death</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://127.0.0.1/about/\">reduction in disease transmission</a>. We have 13 Research Groups spanning these Programmes and we are an international community of over 750 employees, working in more than a dozen locations and working from the molecule to the&nbsp;Ministry of Health, from the bedside to the bench and back as well as in the community.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A recent exciting development has been the rapid uptake and deployment of HIV self-testing to ensure early diagnosis and treatment to prevent HIV transmission. Large scale interventions to increase the diagnosis and treatment of tuberculosis have dramatically reduced TB detection in Malawi but TB remains a major challenge among men and people living with HIV. Our Immunology group is the largest and most vibrant in the region.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Please take a moment to explore our Research Groups’ pages on this&nbsp;website&nbsp; in order to sense the breadth and depth of our research. You might also wish to explore the Wellcome Trust,&nbsp;Liverpool School of Tropical Medicine&nbsp;and&nbsp;University of Liverpool&nbsp;webpages as well as the&nbsp;University of Malawi College of Medicine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We welcome visitors to MLW.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-18 08:46:23', '2020-03-18 08:46:23', '', 9, 'http://127.0.0.1/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(524, 1, '2020-03-18 08:46:48', '2020-03-18 08:46:48', '<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":393,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://127.0.0.1/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/29464931444_a65fde71f8_c.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-393\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Content…\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\"> <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1/programme/preventing-death-from-severe-infections/\">Programme 1: Preventing Death from Infection</a> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->', 'Research', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-18 08:46:48', '2020-03-18 08:46:48', '', 33, 'http://127.0.0.1/33-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(525, 1, '2020-03-18 08:47:13', '2020-03-18 08:47:13', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MLW has an established reputation for providing excellent\nearly career development in a number of strategic disciplines including\nClinical Infectious Diseases, Epidemiology, Immunology, Molecular Microbiology,\nOphthalmology, Public Health, Behavioural Science, Lung Health and Paediatrics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We support the development of African and UK scientists. We\nhave trained 124 scientists – 94 African of which 80 Malawian - in the last 10\nyears.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This reputation allows us to attract the brightest Malawian\nand regional African graduates and retain them in training through to\npostdoctoral level. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to maintain this competitive pipeline and provide a\nfoundation of scientific excellence to support Research Group development and\nproductivity, we propose a central Training and Career Development strategy\nmanaged jointly between MLW and The Malawi College of Medicine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-18 08:47:13', '2020-03-18 08:47:13', '', 60, 'http://127.0.0.1/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(526, 1, '2020-03-18 08:49:31', '2020-03-18 08:49:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MLW has an established reputation for providing excellent\nearly career development in a number of strategic disciplines including\nClinical Infectious Diseases, Epidemiology, Immunology, Molecular Microbiology,\nOphthalmology, Public Health, Behavioural Science, Lung Health and Paediatrics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We support the development of African and UK scientists. We\nhave trained 124 scientists – 94 African of which 80 Malawian - in the last 10\nyears.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This reputation allows us to attract the brightest Malawian\nand regional African graduates and retain them in training through to\npostdoctoral level. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to maintain this competitive pipeline and provide a\nfoundation of scientific excellence to support Research Group development and\nproductivity, we propose a central Training and Career Development strategy\nmanaged jointly between MLW and The Malawi College of Medicine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-18 08:49:31', '2020-03-18 08:49:31', '', 60, 'http://127.0.0.1/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
