(3587, 4, '2020-08-13 18:59:08', '2020-08-13 18:59:08', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>The Training Committee</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The training committee is charged by the Director to the support the high-quality training and professional development of individuals who are working with or who plan to work with the Malawi Liverpool Wellcome Trust (MLW). This is to facilitate the MLW mission to train the next generation of scientists and leaders in research.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Training Strategy</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This strategy aims at:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Identifying training needs through the use of different training needs assessment tools and approaches with the sole aim of closing competency/skills gaps.</li><li>Helping to build effective operational teams which will be able to support the overall MLW goals.</li><li>Identifying and retaining hard to recruit skills and talent</li><li>Building the next generation of managers and leaders who have to be put through the succession pipeline and allows using a similar approach at different levels to ensure continuity.</li><li>Introducing and encouraging new attitudes and behaviours which have to align with the overall future MLW strategic direction.</li><li>Using effective performance management processes which encourage a result oriented working culture.</li><li>Encouraging the transfer of knowledge through proper mentorship and coaching programs.</li><li>Using selective methods to encourage the long-term academic training for critical positions while at the same time encouraging continuous development programs for other role.</li><li>Keeping track of all operational training programmes and using the information for decision making and further improvements.</li><li>Providing a platform for collaborating with other affiliates (College of Medicine, Blantyre Malaria Project-BMP) on collective trainings which may arise from time to time (refer on strategies below last point).</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Operations Training (2017 - 2021)</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MLW institutional goal&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Conduct excellent research to benefit health&nbsp;</li><li>Train the next generation of researchers and scientific leaders Section Goal Training and mentorship to provide excellent, effective operational support to achieve MLWs goal.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Objectives&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• Ensure high performing managers and leaders and succession pipeline to ensure continuity.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• Cultivate a vibrant, high performing work force who effectively contribute to MLW mission.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;• To fully align the research management and infrastructural requirements to the research portfolio to provide an effective al working and learning environment.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ta<strong>rgets&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>• High performing, effective, efficient, resilient operational departments as evidenced by high quality research that offers excellent value for money, and is conducted by qualified staff, according to protocol, in time, and within budget</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Research Training (2017- 2021)</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MLW institutional goal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Leading fundamental and translational research, career development/building, and policy impact aimed at improved health in sub-Saharan Africa through reductions in disease burden and death.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Section Goal&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Research training and mentorship to achieve research excellence and leadership</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Objectives&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>To enable early career researchers to produce world-class scientific research that addresses African health and research priorities</li><li>To optimise institutional scientific research training, mentorship and career pathways</li><li>To cultivate leadership and promote effective scientific collaboration as part of our institutional goal of improving health in sub-Saharan Africa</li><li>To fully align the research management and infrastructural requirements to provide an attractive, vibrant academic environment</li><li>Targets: At least double the MLW core training investment</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Training', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-08-13 18:59:08', '2020-08-13 18:59:08', '', 60, 'http://127.0.0.1/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
