(3611, 4, '2020-08-14 15:10:24', '2020-08-14 15:10:24', 'The Early Life Infection group is made up of paediatricians, obstetricians, public health specialists, infectious disease specialists, social scientists and health economists who propose a collaborative “team science” approach to the development and evaluation of interventions to reduce paediatric mortality secondary to infection.\r\n\r\nOur work is focused on the reduction of the following target indicators;\r\n\r\n(i) adverse birth outcomes\r\n\r\n(ii) perinatal and neonatal mortality and\r\n\r\n(iii) paediatric in-patient mortality.\r\n\r\nOur work has recently evolved to involve an assessment of both the direct and indirect effects of the COVID-19 pandemic on these indicators.', 'Early Life Infection', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'early-life-infection', '', '', '2020-10-19 13:53:55', '2020-10-19 13:53:55', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=research&#038;p=3611', 0, 'research', '', 0),
(3612, 4, '2020-08-14 15:21:05', '2020-08-14 15:21:05', 'Trypanosomiasis and schistosomiasis are two of the neglected tropical diseases with high burden in Malawi. We are investigating the genetic determinants of the human reservoirs of HAT and schistosomiasis and also mapping the areas where these diseases are found, filling an important knowledge gap, while extending and strengthening the underpinning infrastructure to deliver these scientific objectives in particular by developing the next generation of African scientists.\r\n\r\nCurrent Activity\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Site mapping of all schistosomiasis current hot spots for both the parasite and snail hosts</li>\r\n 	<li></li>\r\n 	<li>Identifying active and old cases of trypanosomiasis and determining cytokine profile as a marker for the stages</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Identifying active and old cases of trypanosomiasis and determining genes that makes humans susceptible to infection</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFollowing disease progression of trypanosomiasis Malawi trypanosomiasis HAT strains to understand the uniqueness of the Malawian HAT', 'Neglected Tropical Diseases', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'neglected-tropical-diseases', '', '', '2020-10-19 13:57:13', '2020-10-19 13:57:13', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/?post_type=research&#038;p=3612', 0, 'research', '', 0),
